		<div class="comment_text"><p>Getting rid of the beer gut is the same as any weight loss. Calories burned &gt; calories consumed. The gut is just the last place for it to go away for men. Adding push-ups and sit-ups, or any weight-bearing / resistance exercise, is good because it builds muscle. Muscle burns calories when at rest and when in use. Thus, more muscle burns more calories.</p><p>So does running longer distances or doing any calorie burning exercise more often and for longer periods of time. And consuming fewer calories helps with the amount you have to burn. I hope I wasn't stating the obvious here, just keeping it simple.</p></div>
