		<div class="comment_text"><p>All sound like good goals, Ray. I've also been in the 'lose the gut' resolution crowd for a while... with some decent progress.</p><p>I did notice a couple comments talk about reducing calories to help with this.  If you're doing serious exercise (&gt;= 1 hour a day, 3 times a week or more), you may want to take some time to make a detailed nutrition plan or maybe consult a personal trainer / nutritionist (good PTs are also nutritionists).  At that level of activity, less calories in does not equal more weight out.  In fact, you may be hindering your weight loss progress if you can't finish your workouts or keep up the right pace.  The key is to get the *right* amount of calories daily from 'clean' food sources, while making progress in your workouts to build your muscle mass and reduce the fat (Matt W said this pretty well).</p><p>Don't get discouraged either.  Matt W also has it right where he mentioned that the gut is the last place for results in most men; losing the gut may take some time.</p><p>Good luck with all your resolutions.</p></div>
