		Comment <a href="#c_1713728617">22</a> by Matt W
		posted on 1/4/2011 at 1:14 AM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>P90X is a series of high intensity workouts that target specific muscle groups. It doesn't go by Upper, Middle, Lower, but mixes it up such as chest &amp; legs or biceps &amp; back. One of P90X selling points (and some others like it such as "Insanity") is called muscle confusion. The basic idea here is to change the routine up every 3-4 weeks so your muscles don't get "bored" so to speak and resist growth. Think of it like jumping from JS to CF to SQL to Flex often. You stay fresh on all of the above.</p><p>P90X is a one hour per day, 6 days a week program. It has a three or so routines that all last 90 days (hence the 90). I have not done it, but did some research and may try it one of these days. They did recommend that if you are not used to doing weight bearing or resistance exercises (stretch bands) then you may want to spend some time getting comfortable with that first or even do their less intense series Power 90 (no X).</p><p>One more note if you want to give it a try, look on Craig's List for this or any similar program. You can easily buy it for half price or better.</p></div>
	</div>
